# PromptWars Rubric — Decision Priority

Target **100% in every category**. When tradeoffs occur, apply this order:

1. Problem Statement Alignment
2. Code Quality
3. Security
4. Efficiency
5. Testing
6. Accessibility

Never sacrifice a higher-priority category to improve a lower one.
**Testing and Accessibility are never skipped** — reduce scope elsewhere first.

## Pre-Submit Review (Required)

Before returning any solution, verify all six categories:

| Category | Pass criteria |
|---|---|
| Problem Statement Alignment | Every requirement implemented and verifiable |
| Code Quality | Modular, typed, lint-clean, maintainable |
| Security | Validated inputs, secrets protected, safe errors |
| Efficiency | No redundant work, optimised critical paths |
| Testing | Tests added/updated, `npm test` passes |
| Accessibility | Semantic HTML, ARIA, keyboard, contrast |

If any category fails, fix it before returning the solution.
